{
  "number": 2299,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2299",
  "title": "New widget: Breadcrumb",
  "body": "A few weeks ago, the [breadcrumb](https://community.algolia.com/react-instantsearch/storybook/?selectedKind=Breadcrumb&selectedStory=default&full=0&down=1&left=1&panelRight=1&downPanel=storybooks%2Fstorybook-addon-knobs) was added to the React Instant Search widgets, it helps the user to quickly get where the current page is in relation to the website’s hierarchy. We could also add it to InstantSearch.js library! (This has been discussed a few months ago, see #951) \r\n\r\n### Connector\r\n- [x] Propose an API for the connector\r\n- [x] Implement connector\r\n\r\n### Widget\r\n- [x] Propose an API for the widgets \r\n- [x] Implement the widget \r\n- [x] Decide what to do about the use case with/without the HierarchicalMenu\r\n- [x] Template: `item` and `root` to be able to specify a “Home” label (at the root of the widget)\r\n- [x] Propose a default style \r\n\r\n### Tests & Documentation\r\n- [x] Add story to devnovel\r\n- [x] Add tests\r\n- [x] Write the documentation",
